title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum on 1985-12-31
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) -> Sound Devices 744T (24bit/96k) -> Samplitude Professional v11.03 -> FLAC/16
description:
Set 1

Not Fade Away-> Touch Of Gray, Tons Of Steel, CC Rider, Dupree's Diamond Blues, Cassidy-> Brown Eyed Women, Let It Grow

Set 2

Midnight Hour-> Sugaree, Women Are Smarter, Ship of Fools, Playin' In The Band-> Terrapin Station-> Drums*-> Truckin'-> Black Peter-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E:Not Fade Away-> E: Turn On Your Love Light, E: Brokedown Palace*

*Second Encore* With Baba Olatunji. National Simulcast Nevelle Brothers, then Olatunji Opened

reviews.review_text: hmmmm rushin it a bit I think the boys were hurrying to finish this year up ? saw this show thanx to Janet in the front office had to dance for a minute lol well worth it had 1 for the night before both decent well-played but seemed rushed and short shows. the highlights here are in the Dupree's & Let It Grow in the first & Terrapin & Black Peter although short is pretty sweet.
